After the decision of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Rome to close its churches and chapels and with the Square of St. Peter empty of Christian pilgrims, other religious bodies also cancelled their services and limited public gatherings in churches, mosques, synagogues, temples and gurdwaras.
The Ministry of Health of Iran announced the cancellation of Friday prayers in the areas affected by the outbreak and then the shrines were closed, while Saudi Arabia prohibited the entry of foreign pilgrims and their residents to the sacred places in Mecca and Medina.
The pandemic has caused the most significant change in the global sports calendar since the Second World War.
Most major sporting events were cancelled or postponed, including the 2019–20 UEFA Champions League, the 2019-20 Premier League, the Euro 2020 UEFA, the 2019–20 NBA season and the 2019–20 NHL season.
