On 16 March, the World Health Organization requested an increase in testing programs as the best way to reduce the progress of the VOCID-19 pandemic. High demand for testing due to the widespread spread of the virus resulted in delays of hundreds of thousands of tests in U.S. private laboratories, and supplies of hisopods and chemical reagents were exhausted.
