The testing, supplemented by quarantine of those who achieved positive results and the identification of those with whom they had contacted positive patients at SARS-CoV-2, resulted in satisfactory results.
Researchers working in the Italian city of Vò, the place where the first death occurred by COVID-19 in Italy, carried out two rounds of tests throughout the population of about 3400 inhabitants, with about ten days of difference.
