Other symptoms are fatigue, muscle pain, diarrhoea, sore throat, loss of smell, and abdominal pain.
The time between exposure and onset of symptoms is usually about five days, but may vary between two and fourteen days.
While most cases result in mild symptoms, some progress in viral pneumonia and multi-organic insufficiency.
